	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think I might be able to help you a little...<br><br>Many people have been through those levels, and most will agree that cash gets EXTREMELY tight at times.&nbsp;&nbsp;TO an extent, you've just gonna deal.  Equip doesnt matter so much for a mage, you've got a pet fighting for you :)  But there are a few tips I can give that may be of use...<br><br>1: When cash is tight try not to pass up anything.  That rusty spear or shortsword may not look like much but if you cant afford to put food on the table that's a few hour's rations.<br><br>2:  If you're in the Gfay area, CB is a good source of money and EXP.  The CB belts will sell to players for 1pp each, but it can get REALLY hard to sell them, so you can make a quick trip to Kaladim and find the warrior guild, down underneath that is a dwarf named Canloe [someone], give him CB belts and Leggo pads and he will give you good dorf faction, money and a little armor or weapons, good for money and EXP.<br>Also in kaladim there is a quest (at the cleric guild) to turn in bonechips, this is also a good source of EXP and faction, although Bonechips can also be saved up and sold to player for 2pp-4pp each stack.<br><br>3:  One poster said around your level you should be grouping, and I, ehh, 65% agree ;)  Grouping is always a great asset, but you're a mighty magician :)  You can unleash your elemental fury solo just fine.  Soloing means no splitting loot if you want to be greedy and full EXP.  Around 8th you could start to hunt at Wisp Island (In erud's crossing, on the boat ride from Qeynos to Erudin, seek a TP to Tox forest or maybe one of the karanas and get some maps from EQatlas.com)  Will-o-wisps will be pretty yellow to you and maybe even red, so you might want to hold off until 9 or 10.  They need a magic weapon to hit, so summon a dagger for your pet and yourself.  Rarely, Wisps will drop Greater Light Stones (GLS), which are used for lightsources or a quest in ?west? Karana, at the Gypsy camp.  Find out about this one.  The right gypsy will give you EXP, faction, and a book worth 8pp 6gp, a nice hunk of cash :)<br><br>3:  ...what else...  well, as far as hunting goes, Wisps or CB will take you fast to 10 or 12, around 10 you can start killing the single spawn Siren on Ocean of Tears (boat from FP passes 'tween 2 big rocks, just off the left of the boat and go around the shoreline until you find the lone siren, good EXP, no faction and a 5:00+ spawn time.  She will take you to 15th if you sit there long enough, but it gets boring)  If you dont care about your elf faction (I do), you can hunt Sisters of Erollisi, at Sister Island.  This is the first stop on the Freeport boat.  Sisters here range from 8ish-13ish.  They drop a rusty halberd each kill (good for pet) and a purity belt 90% of the time.  (Sells for 1pp 2gp to vendors, 2-3pp to people.) Hunting here will lower elven faction, and highelf goes down much faster then the Woodelf.  You can still be high amiable to the woodelves you're killing and be apprehencive to your home.  Good money, but at a high price.<br><br>Well, that should do for now anyway :)  Magicians are a powerful class, but soloing gets a little boring.  The best advice I can give is to stick with it, and get ready cause for many people, 12th, 16th and 20th level spells are really bad too.  And after that the hellish magician research begins.  But I can still solo yellows into the mid 20's, so it's all good ;)  Oh, and if you are able to I would STRONGLY STRONGLY suggest going to Lake of Ill Omen in kunar at 15th, you'll be in your 20's before ya know it ;)<br><br>Good luck and have fun! You can ask me any more mage questions via e-mail (rob85@maine.rr.com) if you wish.<br><br>~Zemplokazo, 25th Magi<br>~Masmune, 20th Monk<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
